{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":777,"text":"The following are my opinions,"},{"time":2686,"text":"and do not reflect\nthe opinions or policies"},{"time":4717,"text":"of any particular prosecutor's office."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6725,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":9452,"text":"I am a prosecutor."},{"time":11146,"text":"I believe in law and order."},{"time":12716,"text":"I am the adopted son of a police officer,\na Marine and a hairdresser."},{"time":17139,"text":"I believe in accountability"},{"time":20103,"text":"and that we should all be safe\nin our communities."},{"time":24145,"text":"I love my job"},{"time":26487,"text":"and the people that do it."},{"time":28500,"text":"I just think that it's our responsibility"},{"time":30498,"text":"to do it better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33213,"text":"By a show of hands,"},{"time":35286,"text":"how many of you, by the age of 25,"},{"time":38024,"text":"had either acted up in school,"},{"time":39912,"text":"went somewhere you were\nspecifically told to stay out of,"},{"time":42675,"text":"or drank alcohol before your legal age?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":46409,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":47814,"text":"All right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49520,"text":"How many of you shoplifted,"},{"time":51783,"text":"tried an illegal drug"},{"time":53807,"text":"or got into a physical fight --"},{"time":55510,"text":"yes, even with a sibling?"},{"time":58659,"text":"Now, how many of you\never spent one day in jail"},{"time":62624,"text":"for any of those decisions?"},{"time":69809,"text":"How many of you sitting here today"},{"time":71467,"text":"think that you're a danger to society"},{"time":73302,"text":"or should be defined by those actions\nof youthful indiscretion?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":77907,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":80185,"text":"Point taken."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83504,"text":"When we talk about\ncriminal justice reform,"},{"time":85833,"text":"we often focus on a few things,"},{"time":88379,"text":"and that's what I want\nto talk to you about today."},{"time":92783,"text":"But first I'm going to --\nsince you shared with me,"},{"time":95194,"text":"I'm going to give you\na confession on my part."},{"time":97385,"text":"I went to law school"},{"time":98813,"text":"to make money."},{"time":100725,"text":"I had no interest\nin being a public servant,"},{"time":102820,"text":"I had no interest in criminal law,"},{"time":104531,"text":"and I definitely didn't think\nthat I would ever be a prosecutor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108888,"text":"Near the end of my first year\nof law school, I got an internship"},{"time":111918,"text":"in the Roxbury Division\nof Boston Municipal Court."},{"time":114921,"text":"I knew of Roxbury as an impoverished\nneighborhood in Boston,"},{"time":118465,"text":"plagued by gun violence and drug crime."},{"time":123835,"text":"My life and my legal career changed\nthe first day of that internship."},{"time":129973,"text":"I walked into a courtroom,\nand I saw an auditorium of people"},{"time":133919,"text":"who, one by one, would approach\nthe front of that courtroom"},{"time":136776,"text":"to say two words and two words only:"},{"time":138536,"text":"\"Not guilty.\""},{"time":140352,"text":"They were predominately black and brown."},{"time":144152,"text":"And then a judge, a defense\nattorney and a prosecutor"},{"time":146686,"text":"would make life-altering decisions\nabout that person without their input."},{"time":151571,"text":"They were predominately white."},{"time":155230,"text":"As each person, one by one,\napproached the front of that courtroom,"},{"time":158417,"text":"I couldn't stop but think:"},{"time":160019,"text":"How did they get here?"},{"time":161194,"text":"I wanted to know their stories."},{"time":163773,"text":"And as the prosecutor\nread the facts of each case,"},{"time":167762,"text":"I was thinking to myself,"},{"time":169549,"text":"we could have predicted that."},{"time":172099,"text":"That seems so preventable..."},{"time":175575,"text":"not because I was an expert\nin criminal law,"},{"time":177758,"text":"but because it was common sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181525,"text":"Over the course of the internship,"},{"time":183193,"text":"I began to recognize\npeople in the auditorium,"},{"time":185371,"text":"not because they were\ncriminal masterminds"},{"time":187487,"text":"but because they were\ncoming to us for help"},{"time":189511,"text":"and we were sending them out without any."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193774,"text":"My second year of law school I worked\nas a paralegal for a defense attorney,"},{"time":197377,"text":"and in that experience I met many\nyoung men accused of murder."},{"time":200690,"text":"Even in our \"worst,\" I saw human stories."},{"time":204642,"text":"And they all contained childhood trauma,"},{"time":207542,"text":"victimization, poverty, loss,"},{"time":209802,"text":"disengagement from school,"},{"time":211524,"text":"early interaction with the police\nand the criminal justice system,"},{"time":214683,"text":"all leading to a seat in a courtroom."},{"time":217862,"text":"Those convicted of murder\nwere condemned to die in prison,"},{"time":220876,"text":"and it was during those meetings\nwith those men that I couldn't fathom"},{"time":225018,"text":"why we would spend so much money"},{"time":226829,"text":"to keep this one person in jail\nfor the next 80 years"},{"time":229575,"text":"when we could have reinvested it up front,"},{"time":231606,"text":"and perhaps prevented the whole thing\nfrom happening in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235108,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":240715,"text":"My third year of law school,"},{"time":242084,"text":"I defended people accused\nof small street crimes,"},{"time":244736,"text":"mostly mentally ill,"},{"time":245911,"text":"mostly homeless,"},{"time":247086,"text":"mostly drug-addicted,"},{"time":248261,"text":"all in need of help."},{"time":251194,"text":"They would come to us,"},{"time":252925,"text":"and we would send them away\nwithout that help."},{"time":256557,"text":"They were in need of our assistance."},{"time":260621,"text":"But we weren't giving them any."},{"time":264933,"text":"Prosecuted, adjudged and defended"},{"time":268090,"text":"by people who knew nothing about them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272493,"text":"The staggering inefficiency is what\ndrove me to criminal justice work."},{"time":276425,"text":"The unfairness of it all\nmade me want to be a defender."},{"time":280382,"text":"The power dynamic\nthat I came to understand"},{"time":284156,"text":"made me become a prosecutor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287383,"text":"I don't want to spend a lot of time\ntalking about the problem."},{"time":290338,"text":"We know the criminal justice\nsystem needs reform,"},{"time":292702,"text":"we know there are 2.3 million\npeople in American jails and prisons,"},{"time":295932,"text":"making us the most incarcerated\nnation on the planet."},{"time":298535,"text":"We know there's another seven million\npeople on probation or parole,"},{"time":301836,"text":"we know that the criminal justice system"},{"time":304074,"text":"disproportionately affects\npeople of color,"},{"time":306106,"text":"particularly poor people of color."},{"time":307754,"text":"And we know there are system failures\nhappening everywhere"},{"time":310532,"text":"that bring people to our courtrooms."},{"time":312326,"text":"But what we do not discuss"},{"time":313612,"text":"is how ill-equipped our prosecutors\nare to receive them."},{"time":317151,"text":"When we talk about\ncriminal justice reform,"},{"time":319199,"text":"we, as a society, focus on three things."},{"time":321530,"text":"We complain, we tweet, we protest"},{"time":323366,"text":"about the police, about sentencing laws"},{"time":325519,"text":"and about prison."},{"time":328031,"text":"We rarely, if ever, talk\nabout the prosecutor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334367,"text":"In the fall of 2009,"},{"time":336735,"text":"a young man was arrested\nby the Boston Police Department."},{"time":339785,"text":"He was 18 years old,\nhe was African American"},{"time":342112,"text":"and he was a senior\nat a local public school."},{"time":344706,"text":"He had his sights set on college"},{"time":346654,"text":"but his part-time, minimum-wage job\nwasn't providing the financial opportunity"},{"time":350402,"text":"he needed to enroll in school."},{"time":352709,"text":"In a series of bad decisions,"},{"time":354160,"text":"he stole 30 laptops from a store\nand sold them on the Internet."},{"time":358424,"text":"This led to his arrest"},{"time":359937,"text":"and a criminal complaint\nof 30 felony charges."},{"time":365677,"text":"The potential jail time he faced is what\nstressed Christopher out the most."},{"time":369249,"text":"But what he had little understanding of"},{"time":371367,"text":"was the impact a criminal record\nwould have on his future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376311,"text":"I was standing in arraignments that day"},{"time":378228,"text":"when Christopher's case\ncame across my desk."},{"time":380348,"text":"And at the risk of sounding\ndramatic, in that moment,"},{"time":382888,"text":"I had Christopher's life in my hands."},{"time":385505,"text":"I was 29 years old,\na brand-new prosecutor,"},{"time":387780,"text":"and I had little appreciation\nfor how the decisions I would make"},{"time":390900,"text":"would impact Christopher's life."},{"time":394906,"text":"Christopher's case was a serious one"},{"time":396746,"text":"and it needed to be dealt with as such,"},{"time":398651,"text":"but I didn't think branding him\na felon for the rest of his life"},{"time":401714,"text":"was the right answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404400,"text":"For the most part,\nprosecutors step onto the job"},{"time":406687,"text":"with little appreciation\nof the impact of our decisions,"},{"time":409362,"text":"regardless of our intent."},{"time":410695,"text":"Despite our broad discretion,"},{"time":412234,"text":"we learn to avoid risk at all cost,"},{"time":415430,"text":"rendering our discretion"},{"time":417192,"text":"basically useless."},{"time":419971,"text":"History has conditioned us\nto believe that somehow,"},{"time":422387,"text":"the criminal justice system\nbrings about accountability"},{"time":425198,"text":"and improves public safety,"},{"time":426552,"text":"despite evidence to the contrary."},{"time":429100,"text":"We're judged internally and externally\nby our convictions and our trial wins,"},{"time":432768,"text":"so prosecutors aren't really\nincentivized to be creative"},{"time":436290,"text":"at our case dispositions,"},{"time":438421,"text":"or to take risks on people\nwe might not otherwise."},{"time":442666,"text":"We stick to an outdated method,"},{"time":444187,"text":"counterproductive to achieving\nthe very goal that we all want,"},{"time":447342,"text":"and that's safer communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450004,"text":"Yet most prosecutors standing in my space\nwould have arraigned Christopher."},{"time":454897,"text":"They have little appreciation\nfor what we can do."},{"time":458299,"text":"Arraigning Christopher\nwould give him a criminal record,"},{"time":462426,"text":"making it harder for him to get a job,"},{"time":465020,"text":"setting in motion a cycle"},{"time":466733,"text":"that defines the failing\ncriminal justice system today."},{"time":472073,"text":"With a criminal record and without a job,"},{"time":474082,"text":"Christopher would be unable to find\nemployment, education or stable housing."},{"time":478627,"text":"Without those protective\nfactors in his life,"},{"time":480770,"text":"Christopher would be more likely\nto commit further, more serious crime."},{"time":484164,"text":"The more contact Christopher had\nwith the criminal justice system,"},{"time":487313,"text":"the more likely it would be\nthat he would return again"},{"time":489881,"text":"and again and again --"},{"time":491874,"text":"all at tremendous social cost\nto his children, to his family"},{"time":495702,"text":"and to his peers."},{"time":496877,"text":"And, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":498206,"text":"it is a terrible public safety\noutcome for the rest of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504509,"text":"When I came out of law school,"},{"time":506808,"text":"I did the same thing as everybody else."},{"time":509546,"text":"I came out as a prosecutor\nexpected to do justice,"},{"time":512026,"text":"but I never learned what\njustice was in my classes --"},{"time":514553,"text":"none of us do."},{"time":516203,"text":"None of us do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518960,"text":"And yet, prosecutors\nare the most powerful actors"},{"time":521471,"text":"in the criminal justice system."},{"time":524229,"text":"Our power is virtually boundless."},{"time":525946,"text":"In most cases, not the judge,"},{"time":527423,"text":"not the police, not the legislature,"},{"time":529177,"text":"not the mayor, not the governor,\nnot the President"},{"time":531574,"text":"can tell us how to prosecute our cases."},{"time":535006,"text":"The decision to arraign Christopher\nand give him a criminal record"},{"time":538146,"text":"was exclusively mine."},{"time":540343,"text":"I would choose whether to prosecute\nhim for 30 felonies, for one felony,"},{"time":543853,"text":"for a misdemeanor,"},{"time":545028,"text":"or at all."},{"time":546229,"text":"I would choose whether to leverage\nChristopher into a plea deal"},{"time":549229,"text":"or take the case to trial, and ultimately,"},{"time":551282,"text":"I would be in a position to ask\nfor Christopher to go to jail."},{"time":555920,"text":"These are decisions that prosecutors\nmake every day unfettered,"},{"time":560613,"text":"and we are unaware and untrained"},{"time":563446,"text":"of the grave consequences\nof those decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568498,"text":"One night this past summer,"},{"time":569844,"text":"I was at a small gathering\nof professional men of color"},{"time":573770,"text":"from around the city."},{"time":575381,"text":"As I stood there stuffing\nfree finger sandwiches into my mouth,"},{"time":578362,"text":"as you do as public servant --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":579869,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":580909,"text":"I noticed across the room,"},{"time":582496,"text":"a young man waving and smiling\nat me and approaching me."},{"time":587527,"text":"And I recognized him,\nbut I couldn't place from where,"},{"time":590575,"text":"and before I knew it,\nthis young man was hugging me."},{"time":595134,"text":"And thanking me."},{"time":597766,"text":"\"You cared about me,\nand you changed my life.\""},{"time":601339,"text":"It was Christopher."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603836,"text":"See, I never arraigned Christopher."},{"time":605546,"text":"He never faced a judge or a jail,"},{"time":607170,"text":"he never had a criminal record."},{"time":609133,"text":"Instead, I worked with Christopher;"},{"time":610915,"text":"first on being accountable\nfor his actions,"},{"time":613658,"text":"and then, putting him in a position\nwhere he wouldn't re-offend."},{"time":617665,"text":"We recovered 75 percent\nof the computers that he sold"},{"time":620642,"text":"and gave them back to Best Buy,"},{"time":622169,"text":"and came up with a financial plan"},{"time":623797,"text":"to repay for the computers\nwe couldn't recover."},{"time":626036,"text":"Christopher did community service."},{"time":627775,"text":"He wrote an essay reflecting on how\nthis case could impact his future"},{"time":631078,"text":"and that of the community."},{"time":632453,"text":"He applied to college,"},{"time":633684,"text":"he obtained financial aid,"},{"time":634968,"text":"and he went on to graduate\nfrom a four-year school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638523,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":645574,"text":"After we finished hugging,\nI looked at his name tag,"},{"time":648038,"text":"to learn that Christopher was the manager\nof a large bank in Boston."},{"time":651311,"text":"Christopher had accomplished --\nand making a lot more money than me --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":654635,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":655660,"text":"He had accomplished all of this"},{"time":657190,"text":"in the six years since I had first\nseen him in Roxbury Court."},{"time":660909,"text":"I can't take credit for Christopher's\njourney to success,"},{"time":664731,"text":"but I certainly did my part\nto keep him on the path."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668992,"text":"There are thousands\nof Christophers out there,"},{"time":672593,"text":"some locked in our jails and prisons."},{"time":674398,"text":"We need thousands of prosecutors"},{"time":676287,"text":"to recognize that and to protect them."},{"time":680508,"text":"An employed Christopher is better\nfor public safety than a condemned one."},{"time":684462,"text":"It's a bigger win for all of us."},{"time":688438,"text":"In retrospect, the decision not\nto throw the book at Christopher"},{"time":691543,"text":"makes perfect sense."},{"time":692718,"text":"When I saw him that first day\nin Roxbury Court,"},{"time":694954,"text":"I didn't see a criminal standing there."},{"time":696850,"text":"I saw myself -- a young person\nin need of intervention."},{"time":699669,"text":"As an individual caught selling a large\nquantity of drugs in my late teens,"},{"time":704006,"text":"I knew firsthand the power of opportunity"},{"time":706955,"text":"as opposed to the wrath\nof the criminal justice system."},{"time":712341,"text":"Along the way, with the help\nand guidance of my district attorney,"},{"time":716276,"text":"my supervisor and judges,"},{"time":719273,"text":"I learned the power of the prosecutor"},{"time":721824,"text":"to change lives instead of ruining them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726542,"text":"And that's how we do it in Boston."},{"time":729206,"text":"We helped a woman who was arrested\nfor stealing groceries to feed her kids"},{"time":732775,"text":"get a job."},{"time":734401,"text":"Instead of putting an abused\nteenager in adult jail"},{"time":737573,"text":"for punching another teenager,"},{"time":739050,"text":"we secured mental health treatment\nand community supervision."},{"time":742288,"text":"A runaway girl who was arrested"},{"time":743959,"text":"for prostituting, to survive\non the streets,"},{"time":746086,"text":"needed a safe place to live and grow --"},{"time":748851,"text":"something we could help her with."},{"time":750878,"text":"I even helped a young man"},{"time":752378,"text":"who was so afraid of the older gang kids\nshowing up after school,"},{"time":755505,"text":"that one morning instead\nof a lunchbox into his backpack,"},{"time":758204,"text":"he put a loaded 9-millimeter."},{"time":761467,"text":"We would spend our time that we'd\nnormally take prepping our cases"},{"time":765527,"text":"for months and months\nfor trial down the road"},{"time":767718,"text":"by coming up with real solutions\nto the problems as they presented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772699,"text":"Which is the better way to spend our time?"},{"time":775969,"text":"How would you prefer\nyour prosecutors to spend theirs?"},{"time":779901,"text":"Why are we spending 80 billion dollars"},{"time":782293,"text":"on a prison industry\nthat we know is failing,"},{"time":784759,"text":"when we could take that money\nand reallocate it into education,"},{"time":788347,"text":"into mental health treatment,"},{"time":789780,"text":"into substance abuse treatment"},{"time":791301,"text":"and to community investment\nso we can develop our neighborhoods?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":794383,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":801616,"text":"So why should this matter to you?"},{"time":803244,"text":"Well, one, we're spending a lot of money."},{"time":807294,"text":"Our money."},{"time":809063,"text":"It costs 109,000 dollars in some states"},{"time":811493,"text":"to lock up a teenager for a year,"},{"time":813107,"text":"with a 60 percent chance that that person\nwill return to the very same system."},{"time":817583,"text":"That is a terrible return on investment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822706,"text":"Number two: it's the right thing to do."},{"time":825004,"text":"If prosecutors were a part\nof creating the problem,"},{"time":827983,"text":"it's incumbent on us to create a solution"},{"time":830236,"text":"and we can do that using other disciplines"},{"time":832307,"text":"that have already done the data\nand research for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":834847,"text":"And number three:"},{"time":836040,"text":"your voice and your vote\ncan make that happen."},{"time":838665,"text":"The next time there's a local\ndistrict attorney's election"},{"time":841369,"text":"in your jurisdiction,"},{"time":842545,"text":"ask candidates these questions."},{"time":844063,"text":"One: What are you doing to make\nme and my neighbors safer?"},{"time":847274,"text":"Two: What data are you collecting,"},{"time":849678,"text":"and how are you training your prosecutors"},{"time":851923,"text":"to make sure that it's working?"},{"time":853618,"text":"And number three:"},{"time":854807,"text":"If it's not working for everybody,"},{"time":856687,"text":"what are you doing to fix it?"},{"time":858562,"text":"If they can't answer the questions,"},{"time":860298,"text":"they shouldn't be doing the job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":863480,"text":"Each one of you that raised your hand\nat the beginning of this talk"},{"time":866721,"text":"is a living, breathing example\nof the power of opportunity,"},{"time":870183,"text":"of intervention,"},{"time":871358,"text":"of support"},{"time":872533,"text":"and of love."},{"time":873838,"text":"While each of you may have faced\nyour own brand of discipline"},{"time":876763,"text":"for whatever malfeasances you committed,"},{"time":878900,"text":"barely any of you needed a day in jail"},{"time":880789,"text":"to make you the people\nthat you are today --"},{"time":882892,"text":"some of the greatest minds on the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":885748,"text":"Every day, thousands of times a day,"},{"time":887651,"text":"prosecutors around the United States\nwield power so great"},{"time":890621,"text":"that it can bring about catastrophe"},{"time":892385,"text":"as quickly as it can\nbring about opportunity,"},{"time":894987,"text":"intervention,"},{"time":896243,"text":"support"},{"time":897426,"text":"and yes, even love."},{"time":900758,"text":"Those qualities are the hallmarks\nof a strong community,"},{"time":903688,"text":"and a strong community is a safe one."},{"time":905506,"text":"If our communities are broken,"},{"time":906986,"text":"don't let the lawyers\nthat you elect fix them"},{"time":909107,"text":"with outdated, inefficient,\nexpensive methods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":911314,"text":"Demand more; vote for the prosecutor\nwho's helping people stay out of jail,"},{"time":914981,"text":"not putting them in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916157,"text":"Demand better."},{"time":917332,"text":"You deserve it, your children deserve it,"},{"time":919362,"text":"the people who are tied up\nin the system deserve it,"},{"time":921824,"text":"but most of all,"},{"time":923000,"text":"the people that we are sworn to protect\nand do justice for demand it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926271,"text":"We must,"},{"time":927446,"text":"we must do better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928852,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930033,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":934549,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936012,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":939213,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}